data.description: Looking for a fantastic piece of property to work with? Well, look no further.  8.38 acres, bordered by the Crum Elbow Creek, with a cleared area in the back that is level, private, parklike and walks right out to an expansive opening at the creek. This is without a doubt a hidden jewel, full of potential and waiting for you to write its next chapter.  In the front of the parcel, an 1890's barn that was converted into a single-family home in 1963 with 1,873 SF, 3 bedrooms and 2 baths awaiting restoration. Enter into the first floor to find wood paneled walls, stone surrounding fireplace and an open kitchen with small center island. Two bedrooms with a bathroom in between. The WOW factor happens on the second floor starting with the dramatic, high vaulted ceiling, hand hewn beams, walls of windows on one side, ladder to a loft area on the other, retro wood burning fireplace, two large open rooms and a primary bedroom with full bath attached. What incredible potential with that second floor. From the home you can easily clear a path to the creek, so you not only enjoy the soothing sounds of the babbling brook, but the sights too, not to mention the fly fishing. In the back, there's plenty of space for an accessory structure. Or restore the home back to a barn and build the home of your dreams in the back. With the property zoned NC there is a list of potential commercial/non-residential permitted and special uses, or the potential to subdivide the property. With the mixed-use neighborhood that currently surrounds the property, possibilities are abundant. Located between Routes 9 and 9G, minutes to the Hudson, with Poughkeepsie to the south and Rhinebeck to the north.
